6. I CAN USE ENGLISH LANGUAGE WORDS
An ole man walked slowly down the hill
old: adj
man: N
walked: V
slowly: adv
down: prep
the: definite article
HE SPOKE to a little girl and two boys.Good morning' he said
he: pronoun
a: indefinite article
girl:singular noun
boys: plural noun(more than one)
Good morning: phrase
There are eight words in the first sentence, and thirteen in the second
walk is a regular velb, the past simple is walked
Speak is an irregular verb
the past simple is spoke and the past participle is spoken(the past participle is used to form the present perfect)
